{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:46:05.719441+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, the personal access token provided does not have write permissions to this repository (all three push attempts returned `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token`). I cannot commit the changes.\n\nHowever, here is my complete analysis and the exact changes that **Issue #3** requires:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe issue asks to record a justified false-positive rule waiver in the ZAP baseline configuration and document it. Here's what needs to change:\n\n### 1. `zap/baseline.conf`\n\nThe current file already has rule **10021** (X-Frame-Options Header Not Set) set to `WARN`, but for a **false-positive waiver** the action should be `IGNORE` with a parenthetical reason — this is the standard ZAP baseline config format for suppressing a finding.\n\n**Current content:**\n```\n# OWASP ZAP baseline configuration for local demo app\n# Format: rule_id   action   reason\n10020\tWARN\tMissing anti-clickjacking header is accepted for this local text-only demo.\n```\n\n**Updated content:**\n```\n# OWASP ZAP baseline configuration for local demo app\n# Format: rule_id   action   reason\n10021\tIGNORE(Local demo, false positive)\tX-Frame-Options not needed: the endpoint is a plain-text local demo that never renders third-party content.\n```\n\n> **Why rule 10021 instead of 10020?** Rule **10021** is the ZAP rule for \"X-Frame-Options Header Not Set\" — the classic false-positive for a local-only plain-text demo that never renders HTML frames. Rule 10020 refers to a different alert. The existing entry appears to conflate them; the fix corrects the rule ID and uses `IGNORE` action (the proper waiver action in ZAP baseline format).\n\n### 2. `docs/rule_waivers.md`\n\n**Current content:**\n```\n# Rule Waivers\n\nWaivers must include rule id, action, and local-demo justification.\n```\n\n**Updated content:**\n```\n# Rule Waivers\n\nWaivers must include rule id, action, and local-demo justification.\n\n| Rule ID | Action | Justification |\n|---------|--------|---------------|\n| 10021   | IGNORE (Local demo, false positive) | X-Frame-Options not needed: the endpoint is a plain-text local demo that never renders third-party content. |\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe `Makefile` runs `scripts/validate_repo.py`, which checks for the existence of `zap/baseline.conf` and the content of `run_zap_baseline.sh` (reject non-local targets). Neither of these checks is affected by the changes above, so existing validation will continue to pass.\n\n---\n\n**Limitation:** I was unable to push these changes because the personal access token lacks write access to the repository. A repository admin would need to either grant the token write permissions or apply these changes manually.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 665, "prompt_tokens": 7497, "total_tokens": 8162, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 36, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7104, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007750794, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001965294, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00057855}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865152-aAyuo0OCl7il0BisBbKx", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3d5-b647-7311-aed2-5a547879ac65-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7497, "output_tokens": 665, "total_tokens": 8162, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7104}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 36}}}}]}}}
